  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240°C/ 220°C (fan)/ 475°F/ Gas 9</p>\n<p>Bash the<strong> lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, cut it<span class=\"text-danger\"> [them]</span> down the middle lengthways, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> (keep them for later!) and chop the <strong>softer inner stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> roughly</p>\n<p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Peel the<strong> ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>red </strong><strong>chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, de-seed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>chopped lemongrass innards</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">(can't</span> handle the heat? Go easy!) and chop everything together until you are left with a finely chopped mixture – this is your <strong>aromatic mix </strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> pork mince</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>soy sauce</strong> and the <strong>aromatic mix </strong>and give everything a good mix up </p>\n<p>Divide the<strong> pork mixture</strong> into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> and shape into <strong>meatballs</strong></p>\n<p>Spread the<strong> toasted sesame seeds</strong> over a large board and roll the<strong> meatballs</strong> into the <strong>seeds</strong> to lightly coat them – these are your<strong> pork &amp; sesame meatballs </strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/977.-s-tep-3-x200.jpg",
